# Extra paths Semgrep should skip (beyond its built-in defaults and root .gitignore).
#
# Semgrepignore v2 already applies:
#   - default ignores (node_modules/, build/, dist/, vendor/, .venv/, *.min.js, test(s)/, …)
#   - every .gitignore in the repo (node_modules, dist, build, .rollup.cache, …)
#
# Add lines here only for paths that are still scanned but aren’t worth SAST, e.g.:
#   - semgrep.sarif          CI output (rare self-scan edge case)
#   - **/fixtures/**         large test fixtures
#   - directory/*.json       pure data if it ever triggers false positives
#
semgrep.sarif
